 friends,&quot;  I felt exactly how I felt when I first laid eyes on him, and I remember how he smelled at the beginning of our &quot;date&quot;, and how he looked into my eyes without remorse.<br><br>And as I put my head in my lap, I will remember all of these things all through the night.   I'm glad I managed to get to my room before crying....<br><br>*relationships can hurt...doesn't matter what sex you are.  Sometimes falling in love can be so pointless...* <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udwarkarn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dwarkarn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 2362<br> <font color=#E9D756>(1/29/02 9:12:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2946.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: When the relationship ends... *gender neutral*</span><hr size=1> You will get over it trust me, as humans we have the remarkable ability to move on from things like this after the natural grieving period has ended.<br><br>In fact I believe the only upseting part about a relationship ending is that the routine you have just lived for the past few months/years has been taken away from you, when this happens we tend to mourn for it and want it back for a while.<br><br>Anyway keep your head up and move on, trust me it will happen but only if you want it to.<br><br> <p><center><img src="http://www.users.bigpond.com/raymies/rolelen10.jpg"><BR><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6929">Rolelen Dwarkarn - 56 Myrmidon</a><br><BR><center><a href="http://www.magelo