nd being schmucks.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/bemarr.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=trevalyns>TrevalynS</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#E9D756>(1/29/02 10:05:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2946.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Well...</span><hr size=1> I'm sorry you have to carry this with you. I've dealt with this myself, though on a smaller scale, mainly due to youth. However, I know your pain.<br><br>I really hate when people say let's be friends when they break-up with you. The only thing I could think of when I heard that was that they found someone they liked better, but couldn't think of how to word it.<br><br>I don't believe in friendship after a relationship, however. Most times, they do say it because they think they are being nice, but I believe most times it makes you feel like you're being dragged over sharp, pointy rocks.<br><br>You know you'll get over this, but there's always the question, what if? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/udwarkarn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dwarkarn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 2366<br> <font color=#E9D756>(1/29/02 10:14:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2946.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Well...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I don't believe in friendship after a relationship, however. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>I strongly believe in trying to maintain a friendship after a relationship, I mean weren't you best friends in the said relationship? Why should the friendship change because they found someone they like better? Of course if they cheated on you then poke their eyes out with red hot knitting needles.<br> <p><center><img src="http://www.users.bigpond.com/raymies/rolelen10.jpg"><BR><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6929">Rolelen Dwarkarn - 56 Myrmidon</a><br><BR><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=14125">Hallin Dwarkarn - 37 Druid</a><br><BR><center><a href="http://www.mysticcoercion.cjb.net">Dwarkarnizer - 5 Shaman</a><br><BR><center><a href="http://mysticcoercion.cjb.net">Proud Officer Of Mystic Coercion</a><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ufrostwolfsoulsong.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Frostwolf Soulsong</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.attbi.com/~frostwolf/Sigs/frosticon.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bitch</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#E9D756>(1/29/02 10:57:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2946.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: When the relationship ends... *gender neutral*</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Do people say that to just be nice or do they really think 