b?topicID=2946.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: When the relationship ends... *gender neutral*</span><hr size=1> Friendship after a relationship is very possible depending upon how the relationship ends.  If both partners were in agreement, then it's very possible.  I had an ex-girlfriend in my wedding, and my wife is the sister of another ex.  Both of those relationships ended after a few months on very amicable terms.  No recriminations or hard feelings.  Our time was at an end, and we simply weren't compatible.  It happens.  It sounds like your ex was just a dork that didn't want to bother with a tougher relationship (I'm assuming distance would be a problem, as well as time commitments of law school).<br><br>On a side note, if you can manage it, don't even try to date in law school.  The emotional stuff is too easy to overwhelm you when you are studying 80 hours a week, and you'll have very little time to get involved, anyway.  I mostly didn't date at all during law school, cause it was too much.<br><br>Good luck to you. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ughiastormwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ghia Stormwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 214<br> <font color=#E9D756>(1/29/02 11:28:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2946.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: When the relationship ends... *gender neutral*</span><hr size=1> Well first off I am sorry about him breaking up with you.<br><br>To the others yes it is possible to remain friends with an ex. if it is something both people actually want and are willing to work to try to make it happen.   I dated someone for 2 years in college and we are still friends.  I made a blanket for his daughter when she was a baby.  I cried with him when his wife ended up cheating on him and leaving him. We still email each other and talk on the phone from time to time 12 years after we met.  But like any friendship it takes 2 people willing to work at it.  My ex is unique though I still have to work at most my friendships that are that old to keep in touch but he still keeps in touch too. <br><br>In the beginning though it takes distance to get used to the new relationship lines.  Its really easy to fall into a friends with privileges relationship which isn't good in the long run it is just emotionally draining.  I think that any friendship worth having is one worth working for.  If its the kind of person you got along with and liked you but the timing just wasn't right.  They would likely make a great friend once you have gotten on your feet again after the break up.<br><br>Evelle <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uzariel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zariel</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 208<br> <font color=#E9D756>(1/30/02 1:31:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2946.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: When the relationship ends... *gender neutral*</span><hr size=1> If the ex was bad to you, it's best to cut all ties.  If, however, you had a sad but not unfriendly break-up, it's perfectly possible to remain friends -- if both parties can be mature about it.  My first serious bf and I remained friends after our breakup, because we knew an acrimonious attitude would cause huge problems among our friendship circle.  He's a great guy; it would have been a shame to lose his friendship along with his love.  (Also, his older sister was my best friend at the time.)  I introduced him to his current gf; they've been together for 7 years now.  Since I moved to New England, we've grown apart.  Still, I know if I saw them, things would be cool.<br>Take time for yourself.  Don't start an unecessary fight.  If you can't stand to be near him, don't be.  Be honest with him about your reasons for needing to be alone.  Keep in touch.  If in time you do feel you can see and talk to him without too strong an emotional reaction, you will be glad to have a friend who knows you so well.<br><br>-- Sister Zariel<br> <p><table><tr><td><img src="http://www.lordoftherings.net/images/ca_obloo.jpg" alt="Legolas"></td><td><p><b>Legolas Greenleaf</b></p><p>If I were a character in <A HREF="http://lordoftherings.net/" TARGET="_"><I>The Lord of the Rings</I></A>, I would be Legolas, Elf, a son of the King of Mirkwood.</p><p>In the movie, I am played by <A HREF="http://www.lordoftherings.net/film/cast/ca_obloo.html" TARGET="_">Orlando Bloom</A>.</p><p>Who would <I>you</I> be?<br><A HREF="http://www.zovakware.com/tests/lordoftherings.htm"><small>Zovakware Lord of the Rings Test</small></A>  <small><small>with <A href="http://www.perseus.com/softwareprod/download.html">Perseus Web Survey Software</a></small></small></p></td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uchiteng.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chiteng</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 347<br> <font color=#E9D756>(1/30/02 7:36:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2946.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: When the relationship ends... *gender neutral*</span><hr size=1> If I dont agree with her reasoning, it isnt possible to remain her freind. Not for me.<br>That is because I am suffering pain willfully inflicted, without reason.<br>It doesnt matter (to me) if she feels she has reason. If your broken up,<br>who the hell cares what she feels? At that point what 'I' feel is on top.<br><br>If I DO agree with her reasoning, then it is easily possible. In fact she may have done me a favor by not forcing ME to break up with her. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uluviahoodyhooo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Luvia Hoodyhooo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 136<br> <font color=#E9D756>(1/30/02 9:12:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2946.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: When the relationship ends... *gender neutral*</span><hr size=1> As Chiteng stated in the above post, didn't you say in a previous post that you were planning to break up with the guy once you went to law school?  I'm not saying that this should make him breaking it off with you hurt any less, but perhaps he knew you planned to do it to him so he decided to do it to you first?  That's what I'd do in that situation, break off the relationship on my own terms.<br><br>This being said however, it still sucks to be dumped.<br><br><br>-Luvia <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/bemarr.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rittdabard>rittdabard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#E9D756>(1/30/02 9:36:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2946.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: When the relationship ends... *gender neutral*</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> If I dont agree with her reasoning, it isnt possible to remain her freind. Not for me.<br>That is because I am suffering pain willfully inflicted, without reason.<br>It doesnt matter (to me) if she feels she has reason. If your broken up,<br>who the hell cares what she feels? At that point what 'I' feel is on top.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <br><br>  Therein lays the problem. The pain is willfully inflicted, yes, but it is by YOU. Especially if she has a reason, and I think anything is a good enough reason, so long as she attempts to explain herself. If you no longer give a shit about what she feels after there is nothing in it for you, did you ever really give a shit before she dumped you? I see so many people setting themselves up for there own destruction just so they can show the world what a pretty martyr they are. I have never had pity on a person I respected because I have never respected a pitiful person. Don't misunderstand I do feel empathy for those legitimately fucked sideways. Nobody can hurt you beyond what you allow them. Pleasure and pain go hand in hand. You want to play in the fire I think you have no right to bitch about the burn. <br><br>Ritt<br><br> <br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulurikeen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lurikeen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 256<br> <font color=#E9D756>(1/30/02 9:49:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2946.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: When the relationship ends... *gender neutral*</span><hr size=1> I can feel your pain. Let the hate grow inside you and make you powerful, then come, join the darkside Khamelleon.<br><br>MUwhahahahah!<br><br>J/K <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Smile, your ex is becoming a lawyer. At least you will not have to live with a steenkin lawyer.<br><br>:P <p>Lurikeen Mali'Kyre<BR>Necromancer <BR><BR>"My eyes will pierce your soul, then I will take your life!"<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ukhamelleon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Khamelleon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 82<br> <font color=#E9D756>(1/30/02 9:58:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2946.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: When the relationship ends... *gender neutral*</span><hr size=1> First I want to thank everyone for their comments.  It was really helpful for me to see that other people have been where I have been, and what they decided to do with that situation.  I'm glad many of you were able to remain friends with your ex.<br><br>It was a little ironic, for me.  I've never been in love with any of my other boyfriends.  I never used that word.  Maybe cause most of my relationships didn't last much longer than a month and that didn't give me enough time to get too committed.  But my friends noticed how I acted around him, or how I would talk about them, and kind of tease me about it, saying &quot;Ooooh you are in love!&quot;  Two days ago, and even an hour before we went out, I finally admitted to myself, &quot;Yes I do love him!&quot;  Having it end right after coming to this realization was crushing.  Yes, I was prepared for the relationship to end when law school started.  But a part of me thought, law school is 8 months away or so and by then we would have the bond to make it work during those years.  It would have sucked, it would have been frustrating, but I already knew in my heart he would have been worth it.<br><br>He said he is not good at the long distance relationship and we should get used to being friends.  I just wasn't ready to hear that.  Not NOW.  I could have dealt with it come graduation even, but not NOW.  What is easier for him (not letting himself get soo involved that when I leave its extremely painful) is not easier for me.  For me, I fear that each and every day will dredge on until I leave this place.<br><br>But I think Dwarkarn made a very important point.  About friendship that is.  As did Evelle and Zariel as well.  If I really loved him, then I should want to keep his friendship...no matter what happens.  And I think I will value that relationship, even if nothing else ever comes of it.  ((But how can I prevent myself from being his friend without the hidden intentions of maybe restarting our relationship 3 years from now!!!???))<br><br>Angello- Retired Rogue<br>Khammeleon - Newbie Untwinked Monk<br>Valantine - Lowbie Twinked Rogue<br><br>(OH GOD VALENTINES DAY IS GONNA SUCK!) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uchiteng.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chiteng</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 350<br> <font color=#E9D756>(1/30/02 10:00:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2946.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rittabard</span><hr size=1> So let me get this straight....<br><br>If I am in a four year relationship....<br>And she dumps me for another guy....<br>Because she explains she is dumping me for another guy......<br>That is good enough to expect me to remain freinds??????<br>And of course to not be mad.<br><br>Bullshit.<br><br>Not unless I agree that he is a better guy. Period.<br>But if she WERE honest that is where it would end. I would avoid her at all costs.<br>Never speak to her again. Unless forced. <br>This is NOT being a martyr. This is being what we 'call' 'HUMAN'<br>To expect me to concern myself over what SHE thinks after she just trod<br>on me ego, is TOO MUCH. It wont happen. Your assumption that I must never have<br>cared if I dont, that is trite sophistry. It could be MANY things that prevent it.<br>Like her hurting my feelings for one. You make that rationale so that YOU feel better not so that 'I' feel better. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/bemarr.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rittdabard>rittdabard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 62<br> <font color=#E9D756>(1/30/02 10:06:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2946.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rittabard</span><hr size=1> Lemme ask you this...<br>You loved. Things went afoul. You seperate. At some later point if she needed you as a frined would you be there for her?<br>If not are you saying your love is a conditional or a temporary thing?<br><br>Ritt<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uchiteng.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chiteng</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 351<br> <font color=#E9D756>(1/30/02 10:14:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2946.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rittabard</span><hr size=1> No it can also mean that I have an over-developed sence of justice.<br>If she left 'me' for 'him' she can get her favors from those she gives HERS to.<br>Why should 'I' assist her in any way, when I am cut off, and wounded?<br>It is simple payback. She made the mistake, she can live with it. Perhaps she <br>should make better or different decisions.<br><br>Actually I must confess that I was unable to adhere to the above in reality<br>and I did help one of them to the tune of 12k and no I didnt get anything more than a peck on the cheek. But I do consider that MY weakness.<br>The above remains the ideal. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uglorianafrostglitter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gloriana Frostglitter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 1139<br> <font color=#E9D756>(1/30/02 10:22:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2946.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rittabard</span><hr size=1> *shrug*<br><br>My boyfriend before Ving left me for another woman.  Sure, I was really hurt at first, and very angry.<br><br>Then life kept moving on, I met Ving and was happy, and I realized that while I no longer wanted to date my ex boyfriend, he was still a funny guy that made me laugh so we started talking again.<br><br>I am friends with him and turned out to be very good friends with his present girlfriend (same one he left me for) and I'm sure I will be in their wedding next year.<br><br>Blah blah sense of justice, blah blah.  We weren't right together, we are both very happy with our current amours, by breaking up with me, he did me a favor since I was free when I met Ving.<br><br>Times change, people change, life moves on, the anger fades, the friendship remains (if you're lucky). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/bemarr.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rittdabard>rittdabard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#E9D756>(1/30/02 10:26:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2946.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rittabard</span><hr size=1> Well I am glad to see you don't practice what you preach.<br><br>What you said is that on the condition the relationship ends how you percieve it should, I.E. she doesn't hurt you, only then is she deserving of your continued attentions. Why would I assist her? Because if I ever told her I cared about her I know that that was a statement that was unconditional and nontemporal. That is the ideal to me and I have lived by it also.<br><br>One further thing, could you please clarify what you meant by <br>&quot;when I am cut off&quot; ?<br><br>Ritt<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showMessageRange?topicID=2946.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showMessageRange?topicID=2946.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showPrevMessage?topicID=2946.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com